Description. Male (from Nathan Gorge, Queensland; QM
S 36714
):

Prosoma, dorsal shield . Dorsal profile straight in lateral view (
Fig. 4
); brown, centrally somewhat lighter; very indistinct dark radial pattern (
Fig. 1
); brown setae except around and posterior of eyes; few macrosetae around eyes; one long macroseta below AME.

Eyes (
Fig. 5
). Row of AE procurved and shorter than row of PME.

Pedipalps ( Figs 4 ,
7– 9
). Prolateral tegular lobe very large, median apophysis heavily reduced, membranous (
Fig. 7
); tegular apophysis with three lateral tips, embolus long and slender, tip curled (
Fig. 9
).

Opisthosoma . Dark olive­brown; light median longitudinal band with a cover of white setae; otherwise brown setae (
Fig. 1
). Venter olive­grey; covered with silver­grey setae. Spinnerets olive­brown.

Female (from Boggomoss, Queensland; QM
S 36727
):

Prosoma, eyes, and labium . As male (
Fig. 2
).

Opisthosoma . Olive­brown, light median band less distinct than in males but enhanced by white setae; otherwise brown setae (
Fig. 2
). Venter light brown, setae as male. Spinnerets: Dark brown.

Epigyne, ventral view (
Fig. 10
). Simple sclerotised plate with posterior incision, copulatory ducts visible through integument.

Epigyne, dorsal view (
Fig. 11
). Spermathecae large, ovoid; copulatory ducts not visible in dorsal view.

Distribution. Queensland, north of the McPherson Ranges (
Fig. 12
).
